{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "siscav-api-collection",
		"name": "SISCAV API - Sistema de Controle de Acesso Veicular",
		"description": "Coleção alinhada à API FastAPI em `apps/api/src` (montagem `/api/v1`).\n\n**Ambiente Postman:** importe `SISCAV_API.postman_environment.json` e ajuste `base_url`.\n\n**Fluxo típico:**\n1. `Health Check` → confirmar que a API está no ar.\n2. `Login - Obter Token` (OAuth2 password: `username` = email) → grava `access_token` e `refresh_token`.\n3. Rotas com Bearer usam `{{access_token}}`.\n4. `Refresh Token` → `POST /api/v1/login/refresh-token` com body `refresh_token` (form).\n\n**Seed (`scripts/seed_demo.py`):** `admin@siscav.com` / `admin123` com **is_admin=true** (necessário para **Acionar portão** e **Obter imagem do log**).\n\n**Ingestão de logs (`POST /api/v1/access_logs/`):** se o servidor tiver `DEVICE_INGEST_KEY`, envie header **`X-Device-Key`** (ative o header neste request e preencha `device_ingest_key` no ambiente). Sem chave em `development`/`dev`, a API pode aceitar sem header (ver `deps.verify_device_ingest_key`).\n\n**Rate limits (código atual):** login/refresh **5/min** por IP; registo **100/min** por IP (`auth.py`).\n\n**Rotas `/api/v1/devices/*`:** API de **demonstração**; em `ENVIRONMENT=production` ficam **501** salvo `IOT_DEVICE_DEMO_API=true`.\n\n**Portão:** `POST .../gate_control/trigger` exige JWT de **administrador**; com `GATE_ACTUATOR_URL` vazio a resposta é modo **simulated**.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "siscav-api"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Health & Status",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Root - API Status",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": [""]
						},
						"description": "Endpoint raiz da API. Retorna mensagem de confirmação de que o servidor está online."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Health Check",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/health",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "health"]
						},
						"description": "Verificação de saúde da API. Retorna o status operacional do servidor."
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Endpoints para verificação de status e saúde da API"
		},
		{
			"name": "Autenticação",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Registrar - Criar Conta",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
									"    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"user_id\", jsonData.id);",
									"    console.log(\"Usuário criado com ID: \" + jsonData.id);",
									"    console.log(\"Email: \" + jsonData.email);",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"auth": {
							"type": "noauth"
						},
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"email\": \"novo.usuario@siscav.com\",\n    \"password\": \"senha123456\"\n}",
							"options": {
								"raw": {
									"language": "json"
								}
							}
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/register",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "register"]
						},
						"description": "Regista um novo utilizador (`POST /api/v1/register`).\n\n**Rate limiting (código):** 100 pedidos/minuto por IP (`auth.register`).\n\n**Corpo:** JSON `UserCreate` — `email`, `password` (mín. 8 caracteres).\n\n**Respostas:** 201 + `UserRead`; 409 se o email já existir."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Login - Obter Token",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"access_token\", jsonData.access_token);",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"refresh_token\", jsonData.refresh_token);",
									"    console.log(\"Access token salvo: \" + jsonData.access_token);",
									"    console.log(\"Refresh token salvo: \" + jsonData.refresh_token);",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"auth": {
							"type": "noauth"
						},
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "urlencoded",
							"urlencoded": [
								{
									"key": "username",
									"value": "admin@siscav.com",
									"type": "text",
									"description": "Email do usuário"
								},
								{
									"key": "password",
									"value": "admin123",
									"type": "text",
									"description": "Senha do usuário"
								}
							]
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/login/access-token",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "login", "access-token"]
						},
						"description": "OAuth2 password flow: `POST /api/v1/login/access-token` com `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` (`username` = email, `password`).\n\n**Rate limiting:** 5/min por IP.\n\n**Resposta:** `Token` — `access_token`, `refresh_token`, `token_type=bearer`. Duração configurável no servidor (`ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES`, `REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_DAYS`).\n\nOs testes Postman gravam os tokens no ambiente."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Refresh Token - Renovar Acesso",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"access_token\", jsonData.access_token);",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"refresh_token\", jsonData.refresh_token);",
									"    console.log(\"Tokens renovados com sucesso\");",
									"    console.log(\"Novo access token: \" + jsonData.access_token);",
									"    console.log(\"Novo refresh token: \" + jsonData.refresh_token);",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"auth": {
							"type": "noauth"
						},
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "urlencoded",
							"urlencoded": [
								{
									"key": "refresh_token",
									"value": "{{refresh_token}}",
									"type": "text",
									"description": "Refresh token obtido no login"
								}
							]
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/login/refresh-token",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "login", "refresh-token"]
						},
						"description": "`POST /api/v1/login/refresh-token` com body form `refresh_token` (valor JWT tipo refresh).\n\n**Rate limiting:** 5/min por IP.\n\n**Resposta:** novo par `access_token` + `refresh_token`. Utilizador tem de continuar a existir na base de dados."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Password reset - Pedido",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    var j = pm.response.json();",
									"    if (j.reset_token) {",
									"        pm.environment.set(\"password_reset_token\", j.reset_token);",
									"        console.log(\"password_reset_token guardado no ambiente\");",
									"    }",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"auth": { "type": "noauth" },
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@siscav.com\"\n}",
							"options": {
								"raw": { "language": "json" }
							}
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/password-reset/request",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "password-reset", "request"]
						},
						"description": "`POST /api/v1/password-reset/request` — JSON `{\"email\"}`. Resposta genérica; `reset_token` só vem no JSON se `PASSWORD_RESET_EXPOSE_TOKEN_IN_RESPONSE` estiver ativo (padrão: sim em development, não em production)."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Password reset - Confirmar",
					"request": {
						"auth": { "type": "noauth" },
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"token\": \"{{password_reset_token}}\",\n  \"new_password\": \"novaSenhaSegura123\"\n}",
							"options": {
								"raw": { "language": "json" }
							}
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/password-reset/confirm",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "password-reset", "confirm"]
						},
						"description": "`POST /api/v1/password-reset/confirm` — `token` (JWT do pedido) + `new_password` (mín. 8). Depois faça login com a nova senha."
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Endpoints de autenticação"
		},
		{
			"name": "Whitelist - Placas Autorizadas",
